  "title": "Purchaser",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong>:</p><p>The Purchaser is responsible for the purchase of material, service, tools, equipment, and machinery according to the given demand by various departments. He/she identifies and shortlists potential suppliers and subcon to secure cost-effective sources, and establishes and maintains good relationships with suppliers and subcon to negotiate for the best terms with the shortest possible lead time and up to quality standards.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Source, negotiate, collate quotations and recommend the most competitive suppliers and subcon;</li><li>Review specifications and ensure materials ordered meet proper quality standard and comply to contract specifications;</li><li>Maintain records of goods ordered and received;</li><li>Maintain and update the approved supplier list;</li><li>Compile supplier performance report for completed projects;</li><li>Adhere closely to Company’s purchasing procedures and ISO standards.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong>:</p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least Diploma in relevant discipline;</li><li>3 years in building construction industry</li><li>Familiar with building construction materials</li><li>Knowledge of ERP System will be an advantage</li><li>Knowledge of M&E materials will be an advantage</li><li>Have excellent negotiation skills;</li></ul><p></p><p>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply this position via Apply Now button or email to <u><strong>Career@kah.com.sg</strong></u></p><p><em>Only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</em></p><p><br /></p>",
